WEBVTT

00:06.206 --> 00:08.333
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

00:08.508 --> 00:09.736
<i>FRANKIE:
Yep, that's me...</i>

00:09.909 --> 00:12.878
<i>...trapped in an office supply store
at 4 in the morning.</i>

00:13.046 --> 00:14.536
<i>How'd I end up here?</i>

00:14.714 --> 00:17.205
<i>How does anyone end up anywhere
they don't wanna be?</i>

00:17.384 --> 00:18.442
<i>Either drugs or kids.</i>

00:18.618 --> 00:20.586
How do I look? I can take it.

00:21.221 --> 00:24.588
I need some constructive criticism.
Tryouts are Thursday.

00:24.758 --> 00:27.784
What would impress the judges?
If you lit the ends on fire.

00:27.994 --> 00:29.393
This is a serious sport, Axl.

00:29.562 --> 00:33.054
They don't just let anyone wear
the white patent-leather boots.

00:33.233 --> 00:34.530
[GLASS BREAKING]

00:34.701 --> 00:36.601
Oh, man, that would have been
so much cooler on fire.

00:36.770 --> 00:39.762
Whoa, I thought you were babysitting
for the Craigs Thursday night.

00:39.939 --> 00:41.201
I'm gonna have to cancel.

00:41.374 --> 00:42.898
Are you sure that's a good idea?

00:43.076 --> 00:45.374
Don't know what's gonna happen
with majorettes.

00:45.545 --> 00:48.639
But if you go to babysitting
at least you'll have six dollars.

00:48.815 --> 00:52.307
Mom, with the swine flu outbreak
I have a real shot this year.

00:52.519 --> 00:55.317
A lot of good people are down.

00:56.289 --> 00:57.722
FRANKIE:
Brick?

00:57.891 --> 01:00.291
That's right.
It's hat day next week.

01:00.460 --> 01:03.429
Good job staying ahead of schedule.
That's a crazy hat.

01:03.596 --> 01:07.532
It's hat day next week?
Oh, no, I need a hat.

01:07.734 --> 01:09.929
- Uh, Brick?
- This isn't for hat day.

01:10.103 --> 01:11.434
That would be embarrassing.

01:11.604 --> 01:13.765
I wanted people to pay attention
at breakfast.

01:13.940 --> 01:16.170
Yesterday, none of you
said a single word to me.

01:16.342 --> 01:19.004
Axl, you're coming straight home
after school...

01:19.179 --> 01:20.806
...to work on your Aztec report.

01:20.980 --> 01:23.949
- God. Chill. I'm on it.
FRANKIE: Oh, are you?

01:24.117 --> 01:26.745
"Twelve to 15 pages,
double spaced.

01:26.920 --> 01:29.013
No fewer than six color charts
or graphs...

01:29.189 --> 01:32.920
...bound in an Oxford
ReadyClip clear-front report cover."

01:33.093 --> 01:37.154
Mr. Gottlieb is tough. He's not gonna
pass you so you can play basketball.

01:37.330 --> 01:40.663
Yeah, I know. Parents need to talk
to him. He's got no school spirit.

01:40.834 --> 01:43.667
FRANKIE:
Axl, this is 40 percent of your grade.

01:43.837 --> 01:47.773
- You do get that's almost half, right?
- The paper's not due for a week.

01:47.941 --> 01:49.135
You treat me like a kid.

01:49.309 --> 01:51.539
- I'm practically an adult.
FRANKIE: In what way?

01:51.711 --> 01:53.770
You don't make your food,
buy your clothes.

01:53.947 --> 01:56.814
You don't remember to flush
the toilet unless I remind you.

01:56.983 --> 01:59.850
- I'm almost old enough to go to war.
- Not if we wanna win.

02:00.019 --> 02:03.216
- Dad, how do you live with her?
- By doing what she says.

02:03.389 --> 02:05.482
- You will do the same.
- Ugh, you are so annoying.

02:05.658 --> 02:07.888
You live to make me miserable.

02:09.963 --> 02:13.660
Maybe we should call that one
a write-off and just work on the others.

02:17.637 --> 02:19.298
- So guess what?
- Hm?

02:19.472 --> 02:23.670
Charlotte and I are having
our three-week anniversary.

02:24.177 --> 02:26.805
- Wanna see a picture of her?
- Really? Yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:26.980 --> 02:30.177
- So are you two getting serious?
- Well, if by "serious" you mean...

02:30.350 --> 02:33.547
...madly in love,
I'd have to say guilty.

02:33.720 --> 02:35.551
- Yay.
- Yeah, yeah.

02:35.722 --> 02:36.848
Here's another one.

02:37.891 --> 02:40.223
- I can't show you that one. It's private.
- Okay.

02:40.393 --> 02:42.725
Here's a good one.
I'll forward it to your phone.

02:42.896 --> 02:45.558
My phone cost, like, a dollar.
It doesn't do that stuff.

02:45.732 --> 02:46.926
Sure it does.

02:47.133 --> 02:48.191
[PHONE BEEPS]

02:48.401 --> 02:51.370
- See.
- Oh, my God. I had no idea.

02:51.538 --> 02:54.234
- Oh, you sent me the wrong one.
- Oh, yeah, okay.

02:54.407 --> 02:56.238
And it takes pictures.

02:56.409 --> 02:57.433
Smile.

02:57.644 --> 02:59.111
- And movies.
- No way.

02:59.279 --> 03:01.873
You can make your own movies,
put faces on thimbles...

03:02.048 --> 03:04.380
...act out your prom
the way it should have gone.

03:04.551 --> 03:06.610
It's very cathartic.

03:06.786 --> 03:08.413
I hear.

03:11.090 --> 03:15.686
Axl, why is your textbook in the
exact position it was in this morning?

03:15.862 --> 03:18.797
- It hasn't moved.
- There. It's moved. Happy?

03:18.965 --> 03:21.229
Hey. You watch your tone, mister.

03:21.401 --> 03:24.564
What tone?
You're always imagining this tone. Ugh.

03:24.737 --> 03:26.762
Why do you have to ride me
all the time?

03:26.940 --> 03:32.139
<i>FRANKIE: And then I got an idea.
A brilliant, glorious idea.</i>

03:32.312 --> 03:35.213
<i>I would film my kids
and show them what they sounded like.</i>

03:35.381 --> 03:37.576
- until you achieve
total mind control?

03:38.418 --> 03:41.945
Honey.
Can you please not twirl in the house?

03:42.121 --> 03:43.884
Well, where am I supposed to do it?

03:44.057 --> 03:46.992
It's too cold outside
and my fingers freeze up...

03:47.193 --> 03:49.889
...and if I can't practice,
then I won't make the team...

03:50.063 --> 03:52.554
...and it will be all your fault!

03:52.732 --> 03:55.895
Brick, your dad's going to the mall.

03:56.069 --> 03:57.969
You wanna go with him
to look for a hat?

04:01.574 --> 04:03.405
Brick?

04:03.576 --> 04:05.203
Any response would be nice.

04:06.946 --> 04:10.347
<i>FRANKIE: And once I started,
I couldn't stop. This thing was power.</i>

04:10.516 --> 04:12.074
God, I hear you.

04:12.252 --> 04:14.686
"Do your paper."
"Have you done your paper?"

04:14.854 --> 04:16.253
- I will!
- I did!

04:16.422 --> 04:17.753
- I am!
- Ugh!

04:17.957 --> 04:19.481
- Ugh!
- Ugh!

04:23.129 --> 04:26.121
<i>FRANKIE: After several days of collecting
evidence, it was show time.</i>

04:26.633 --> 04:28.362
<i>I wasn't doing this for myself.</i>

04:28.534 --> 04:31.332
<i>I was doing it for moms
through the ages who'd had enough.</i>

04:31.504 --> 04:33.734
- Hey, honey.
- Hey, Mike.

04:34.474 --> 04:35.873
Oh, hey, Bob.

04:36.042 --> 04:38.442
Bob was helping me set up
that thing...

04:38.611 --> 04:40.340
...that I wanna show the kids.
- Oh.

04:40.513 --> 04:41.844
How long's that gonna take?

04:42.015 --> 04:45.212
<i>FRANKIE: I had long ago accepted Mike
and Bob weren't gonna ever be friends.</i>

04:45.385 --> 04:48.616
<i>It's not that Mike didn't like Bob,
it's just...</i>

04:48.788 --> 04:50.278
<i>Yeah, he just didn't like him.</i>

04:50.456 --> 04:54.324
So. Michael Michael Bo-Bichael.
Ha-ha-ha.

04:54.494 --> 04:56.257
How goeth the job search?

04:56.496 --> 04:57.861
[GRUNTS]

04:58.498 --> 05:01.797
Little slow. That's why
I like to come home and relax.

05:01.968 --> 05:05.233
Hey. I'm an idiot.
Why didn't I think of this?

05:05.405 --> 05:07.635
The guy riding shotgun
on my night shift...

05:07.807 --> 05:10.640
...delivering Little Betty snack cakes
just quit.

05:10.810 --> 05:12.971
If you're interested,
I can put your name in.

05:13.146 --> 05:15.011
It's union pay. Easy gig.

05:15.181 --> 05:18.014
I don't know, Bob.
I wouldn't wanna put you out.

05:18.184 --> 05:21.153
Union pay. Easy gig. Mike.

05:21.321 --> 05:23.084
Sounds great.

05:23.289 --> 05:25.052
- Riding with you, huh?
- Yeah.

05:25.224 --> 05:27.215
Kids, can you come in here?

05:27.393 --> 05:29.657
Come on, everybody.
Come on in. Sit down.

05:29.829 --> 05:31.558
Everybody, sit down.

05:31.731 --> 05:35.599
Okay. We are gonna watch
some educational television.

05:35.802 --> 05:38.168
Now, there's been some
bad behavior going on.

05:38.338 --> 05:40.932
I think it's time
I brought it to your attention...

05:41.107 --> 05:45.840
...and I must warn you,
what you are about to see is not pretty.

05:48.915 --> 05:51.577
<i>Seriously. When did you
hatch this plan to ruin my life?</i>

05:51.751 --> 05:53.048
Hey, you recorded me?

05:53.219 --> 05:55.710
<i>- make me do
is make me some mindless zombie here...</i>

05:55.888 --> 05:57.856
<i>FRANKIE [ON SCREEN]:
I don't have to destroy your life, Axl.</i>

05:58.024 --> 06:01.084
<i>Because you're doing a pretty
damn good job of it yourself.</i>

06:01.260 --> 06:04.229
<i>Hey. Time is passing, Axl!</i>

06:04.397 --> 06:06.627
Okay. Wait. That's the wrong spot.

06:06.833 --> 06:07.959
<i>FRANKIE [ON SCREEN]:
I did my homework!</i>

06:08.134 --> 06:10.932
<i>Why do I have to do
your homework?</i>

06:12.271 --> 06:13.295
Okay. There we go.

06:13.473 --> 06:15.941
<i>...and it will be all your fault!</i>

06:16.743 --> 06:18.233
Not so pretty, Sue, is it? Hm?

06:18.711 --> 06:21.771
<i>My fault?
Why is everything my fault?</i>

06:21.948 --> 06:24.439
<i>It'll be my fault
if you forget to call Mrs. Craig...</i>

06:24.617 --> 06:26.915
<i>...and tell her you can't sit
on Thursday?</i>

06:27.086 --> 06:29.281
<i>Am I talking for my own health here?</i>

06:29.455 --> 06:31.923
Wait, wait, wait. That's wrong.

06:32.091 --> 06:35.060
<i>All you have to do
is flush the toilet and do your homework.</i>

06:35.228 --> 06:37.890
<i>Do you have any idea
how lucky you are? Do you? Do you?</i>

06:38.064 --> 06:41.830
<i>Someday I'll be dead
and you'll wish you could hear my voice!</i>

06:42.001 --> 06:46.335
<i>This is the last time I'm telling you!
I'm not telling you again!</i>

06:46.506 --> 06:50.670
<i>I will not say this one more time!</i>

06:58.951 --> 07:02.387
So let that be a lesson to you.

07:08.694 --> 07:09.854
FRANKIE:
It's not my fault.

07:10.029 --> 07:13.021
The kids don't listen to me
unless I yell at them.

07:13.199 --> 07:16.259
I'm tired, and they push me.
Mike, you see how they push me.

07:16.436 --> 07:18.301
They do. They're horrible.

07:18.504 --> 07:21.064
Horrible, horrible children.

07:22.208 --> 07:24.699
This is not who I wanted to be.

07:24.877 --> 07:27.778
Well, it's too late now.
Night, honey.

07:29.000 --> 07:35.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

07:36.456 --> 07:38.617
I'm gonna change.

07:38.791 --> 07:41.919
No, no, don't change.

07:42.094 --> 07:44.824
- I am. I'm gonna quit yelling.
- Hm.

07:45.031 --> 07:46.430
What? You don't think I can?

07:46.599 --> 07:48.430
It's gonna be like
when you quit sugar.

07:48.601 --> 07:50.501
I found you on the bathroom floor...

07:50.670 --> 07:52.433
...sucking frosting out of the tube.

07:52.605 --> 07:55.472
I don't want my kids growing up
and saying to some shrink:

07:55.641 --> 07:58.439
"Yeah, all my mom ever did
my whole life was yell at me."

07:59.045 --> 08:00.137
[LAUGHS]

08:00.346 --> 08:03.076
They're not gonna be able
to afford a shrink.

08:06.185 --> 08:08.346
Okay, guys.

08:08.554 --> 08:12.012
I've decided I don't like the way
I sound on the tape.

08:12.191 --> 08:14.489
It seems like once in a while
I raise my voice...

08:14.660 --> 08:16.685
Once in a while
you don't raise your voice.

08:16.863 --> 08:20.355
Okay, the point is,
we've gotten into a bad pattern.

08:20.566 --> 08:23.126
I nag, you don't listen
and I end up yelling.

08:23.302 --> 08:28.205
So from now on, I will calmly ask you
to do something once.

08:28.374 --> 08:32.174
Then you'll show me you can listen
and I'll show you I don't need to yell.

08:32.345 --> 08:33.812
So you're gonna stop nagging?

08:33.980 --> 08:37.711
I'm gonna start trusting
that you can do the things I ask you to.

08:37.884 --> 08:40.182
- What do we get?
- It doesn't work that way.

08:40.352 --> 08:42.981
- We should get something.
- Not what this is about.

08:43.155 --> 08:45.214
- How about a Tootsie Roll?
- Oh, I like waffles.

08:45.391 --> 08:46.858
We should get money.

08:47.026 --> 08:49.324
This is not some kind of contest
for prizes.

08:49.495 --> 08:53.522
This is about us becoming the family
where the mother doesn't have to yell!

08:55.868 --> 08:57.699
Starting now.

08:59.805 --> 09:02.205
I trust them,
then they'll feel respected...

09:02.375 --> 09:05.401
...and then respect me in return
by doing what they're told.

09:05.611 --> 09:06.976
It's like a trust circle.

09:07.146 --> 09:11.480
Actually, a trust-respect circle.
Or is that an oval? I don't know.

09:11.651 --> 09:14.586
A whole new concept,
so we're trying to figure out the shape.

09:14.754 --> 09:15.846
Yeah.

09:16.022 --> 09:17.148
[PHONE BEEPING]

09:17.323 --> 09:19.382
- That'll be my special lady.
- Oh!

09:19.559 --> 09:21.254
Wait. It's my boss at Little Betty.

09:21.427 --> 09:24.225
He's willing to hire Mike
to drive the late shift with me.

09:24.397 --> 09:29.562
That's great. Oh, my gosh.
Mike will be so excited.

09:30.703 --> 09:31.829
Why don't you tell him?

09:36.042 --> 09:37.236
[PHONE RINGS]

09:38.244 --> 09:40.872
<i>- Hey.
BOB: Hey. Axl, it's Bob.</i>

09:41.047 --> 09:43.277
Axl's home?
He's supposed to be at the library.

09:43.449 --> 09:45.713
Ask him if he's working
on his Aztec paper.

09:45.885 --> 09:47.682
So...

09:48.354 --> 09:50.652
...what you doing there, buddy?

09:51.791 --> 09:54.351
Nothing. Just hanging out.

09:54.527 --> 09:55.926
Is he watching TV?

09:56.095 --> 09:58.063
So you...

09:58.230 --> 09:59.925
You watching TV?

10:01.033 --> 10:02.864
This is getting kind of creepy, Bob.

10:03.569 --> 10:07.027
Ask him to tell you the difference
between the Mayan and Aztec cultures.

10:07.740 --> 10:10.971
I don't know how to work that naturally
into the conversation.

10:11.177 --> 10:15.409
- Bob, are you talking to my mother?
- No, haven't seen her. Bye.

10:16.282 --> 10:18.443
I think he's on to us.

10:21.287 --> 10:23.278
[MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]

10:24.924 --> 10:27.825
<i>FRANKIE: This was gonna be harder
than I thought. Days were passing.</i>

10:27.994 --> 10:30.224
<i>Who knew if they were living up
to the deal.</i>

10:30.396 --> 10:32.796
<i>They weren't saying anything
and I couldn't ask.</i>

10:32.965 --> 10:37.129
Hey. There's my hard-working kids.

10:38.270 --> 10:40.966
[PEOPLE CHEERING ON TV]

10:41.140 --> 10:45.474
Hey, there's my kids.

10:48.748 --> 10:53.651
There's a lot on TV this week, huh?

10:53.819 --> 10:57.186
<i>FRANKIE: The urge to yell and nag
was building, but that's okay.</i>

10:57.356 --> 10:59.722
<i>I knew how to deal with it.</i>

11:07.333 --> 11:10.097
<i>FRANKIE: Mike was getting ready for
his first night on the job...</i>

11:10.269 --> 11:13.261
<i>...and I'd gone three whole days
without screaming at my kids.</i>

11:13.439 --> 11:16.203
<i>Hard to say
who was more miserable.</i>

11:16.375 --> 11:17.740
<i>Ah, hell, it was me.</i>

11:18.277 --> 11:20.211
I'm itchy, my stomach aches...

11:20.379 --> 11:23.644
...and my jaw hurts
from all the clenching.

11:23.816 --> 11:27.149
God, I wanna yell.
I wanna yell so bad.

11:27.319 --> 11:29.014
You're going through withdrawal.

11:29.188 --> 11:34.490
Mike, it's not that I enjoy yelling.
I do it for the children.

11:34.660 --> 11:37.652
That's what junkies do.
Anything to justify the next fix.

11:37.830 --> 11:41.322
Pretty tough talk coming from a guy
with a cupcake on his shirt.

11:42.201 --> 11:45.534
All I'm saying is, whatever happened
to the whole trust circle thing?

11:45.705 --> 11:47.036
It's a trust-respect oval...

11:47.206 --> 11:49.697
...and what happened is,
is that it's a load of crap.

11:49.875 --> 11:51.740
You said
you wanted to trust the kids.

11:51.911 --> 11:54.641
Why don't you try doing it.
They might surprise you.

11:54.814 --> 11:56.907
This morning Sue
was cleaning her room.

11:57.083 --> 11:59.074
- Really?
MIKE: They're growing up, Frankie.

11:59.285 --> 12:02.482
Cut yourself some slack
and focus on what's really important.

12:02.655 --> 12:03.815
Helping me figure out...

12:03.989 --> 12:07.982
...how the hell I'm gonna get through
a whole night stuck in a truck with Bob.

12:10.496 --> 12:12.589
<i>FRANKIE: So yeah, Mike thought
the kids had grown up.</i>

12:12.798 --> 12:16.825
<i>But he said that as soon as we
brought them home from the hospital.</i>

12:17.369 --> 12:18.393
<i>But then...</i>

12:19.505 --> 12:22.702
Brick, where'd you get that hat?
I thought you didn't have one.

12:22.875 --> 12:25.435
Got it myself.
Wore it to hat day.

12:25.611 --> 12:28.045
Was the coolest kid in school.

12:28.214 --> 12:29.681
[WHISPERING]
Coolest kid.

12:29.882 --> 12:31.349
[CAR HORN HONKS]

12:31.584 --> 12:33.882
That's my ride.
Going to majorette tryouts.

12:34.053 --> 12:38.752
- You arranged your own ride?
- Yep. Wish me luck.

12:43.262 --> 12:46.231
<i>FRANKIE: Wow. And just when I thought
it couldn't get any better...</i>

12:47.233 --> 12:49.599
<i>...the best
and most amazing thing of all...</i>

12:49.769 --> 12:53.637
<i>...Axl was writing his history paper.
On his own.</i>

12:53.839 --> 12:56.774
<i>Without any nagging
or yelling from me.</i>

12:59.078 --> 13:01.410
Welcome to my time, Mike.

13:01.580 --> 13:05.448
The town begins to sleep
and we can prowl in the silence.

13:05.618 --> 13:07.449
Yeah, I can't really hear the silence.

13:07.653 --> 13:08.813
[PHONE BEEPS]

13:08.988 --> 13:11.582
Oh, look at that.
My lady owl awakes.

13:12.424 --> 13:13.982
Hey there, pretty bird.

13:14.160 --> 13:18.824
First night on the road
with my BFF Mike.

13:18.998 --> 13:20.829
Sure you should do that
while you drive?

13:21.000 --> 13:23.298
It's fine. I'm a fast texter.

13:23.502 --> 13:24.969
[CAR HORN BLARES]

13:25.371 --> 13:28.670
Bob, knock it off and drive.

13:31.177 --> 13:32.269
[PHONE BEEPS]

13:32.444 --> 13:33.638
Oh!

13:35.247 --> 13:36.339
- Read it to me.
- No.

13:36.515 --> 13:37.846
Come on. What does she say?

13:38.017 --> 13:40.247
[TRUCK HORN BLARES]

13:41.754 --> 13:46.657
"Hey, Bobby beast-boy."
Since you're swerving anyway...

13:46.826 --> 13:50.159
...can you find a bridge or something
and make it quick?

13:54.533 --> 13:57.832
<i>FRANKIE: Turns out Mike was right.
The kids had surprised me.</i>

13:58.003 --> 14:00.528
<i>I felt this new sense of freedom
opening up for me...</i>

14:00.706 --> 14:02.367
<i>...endless possibilities.</i>

14:02.541 --> 14:05.977
<i>Like finally using those bath salts
I got for Mother's Day.</i>

14:08.647 --> 14:10.842
<i>2001.</i>

14:14.320 --> 14:15.412
[DOORBELL RINGS]

14:16.689 --> 14:18.816
Can somebody get that?

14:19.992 --> 14:21.118
[DOORBELL RINGS]

14:21.327 --> 14:23.192
Has anybody got it?

14:25.297 --> 14:27.993
Hello?
Can anybody hear the doorbell?

14:28.167 --> 14:30.067
Yeah, it's really annoying.

14:31.370 --> 14:33.565
Hey, Frankie.
We're late for Kiwanis.

14:33.739 --> 14:37.140
Sue was supposed to be at my house
an hour ago to baby-sit.

14:37.309 --> 14:40.005
What? But she's at baton tryouts.

14:40.179 --> 14:42.374
She called you to cancel.

14:42.548 --> 14:44.539
- Didn't she?
- No, she didn't.

14:44.717 --> 14:47.880
You could have reminded her, Frankie.
She's only a child.

14:48.053 --> 14:51.545
Here, I'll be back in a couple hours.

14:53.859 --> 14:54.951
[SIGHS]

14:55.828 --> 14:58.319
Brick. Can you sit with the baby
while I get dressed?

14:58.497 --> 15:00.988
That might not be a good idea.
It could get my lice.

15:01.166 --> 15:03.396
- Your what?
- Oh, yeah.

15:03.569 --> 15:05.537
My teacher told me
to give you this note.

15:05.704 --> 15:08.195
Brick, where did you get that hat?

15:08.374 --> 15:12.003
You forgot to remind me to take a hat
on Tuesday, so I didn't have one.

15:12.177 --> 15:14.873
But then I saw this homeless guy
going through the trash.

15:15.047 --> 15:16.514
So I traded him my banana for it.

15:16.682 --> 15:18.081
[WHISPERING]
Banana.

15:18.250 --> 15:20.343
FRANKIE:
Oh, my God.

15:20.519 --> 15:22.953
Take that thing off
and put it in the trash.

15:23.122 --> 15:26.057
Everybody stay away from Brick's head.
Axl, I need your help.

15:26.225 --> 15:29.626
- Burn all the sheets, scrub the house.
- Aztec paper's due tomorrow.

15:29.795 --> 15:31.626
What? I thought
that was due next week.

15:31.797 --> 15:33.287
Yeah. I wrote that down wrong.

15:33.499 --> 15:35.433
You're just starting to work
on this now?

15:35.601 --> 15:39.230
I told you this is 40 percent
of your grade. It's your future.

15:39.405 --> 15:41.464
I've been working on it
for the last hour.

15:41.640 --> 15:43.198
Do you have all the supplies?

15:43.375 --> 15:46.742
It says specifically "an Oxford
ReadyClip clear-front report cover."

15:46.912 --> 15:49.244
- Don't we have one of those?
- I told you.

15:49.415 --> 15:51.906
If I can't steal it from Ehlert's,
we don't have it.

15:52.084 --> 15:55.383
Okay, I admit it. I screwed up.
Go ahead, yell at me.

15:55.554 --> 15:57.715
You'd like that now.
I don't have the luxury.

15:57.890 --> 16:00.723
I've 11 minutes to get
to Office Warehouse before it closes.

16:00.893 --> 16:03.953
I cannot believe
how irresponsible you are.

16:04.129 --> 16:06.029
Watch this baby.

16:12.271 --> 16:13.602
[CRYING]

16:17.676 --> 16:18.836
[PHONE BEEPS]

16:19.044 --> 16:20.978
Oh, she's back, she's back.

16:21.146 --> 16:23.137
Tell me what she says.

16:23.315 --> 16:26.842
- "I don't think this is working."
- Really?

16:27.052 --> 16:30.283
- It's a brand-new phone.
- No, that's what she said.

16:30.456 --> 16:33.323
"You're a nice guy, but I think..."

16:34.560 --> 16:37.324
Hey, how about I turn this off
until after we finish?

16:37.496 --> 16:40.090
What? Why? What'd she say?

16:40.699 --> 16:42.667
It seems like she's breaking up
with you.

16:42.835 --> 16:46.362
- Why? Why?
- I don't know.

16:46.572 --> 16:48.540
You know who's good
at talking about this?

16:48.707 --> 16:52.006
- Anybody else.
- Read it to me. Read me more.

16:52.177 --> 16:54.509
This is personal.
You should read it yourself.

16:54.680 --> 16:56.170
I can't.

16:56.782 --> 17:00.115
I can't see anything
through the tears.

17:22.340 --> 17:24.205
Yes.

17:31.617 --> 17:34.484
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

17:39.658 --> 17:42.320
It's my fault. I got on her nerves.

17:42.494 --> 17:44.519
I texted her every 10 minutes.

17:53.038 --> 17:55.598
Look, Bob,
there's a lot of girls in the world.

17:55.774 --> 17:58.140
Oh, sure, says the seven-foot god.

17:59.344 --> 18:01.938
- What's wrong with me?
- I don't know.

18:02.147 --> 18:04.411
Sometimes you're a little needy.

18:04.583 --> 18:07.211
Oh, my God, I'm needy?

18:10.289 --> 18:11.381
[CRIES]

18:12.591 --> 18:13.888
Damn it.

18:14.560 --> 18:15.754
[SCREAMING]

18:22.935 --> 18:26.735
Ah, get off me.
Haven't I suffered enough?

18:26.905 --> 18:28.964
I'll get off
if you promise to calm down.

18:29.174 --> 18:31.199
I promise. Just let me sit up.

18:38.050 --> 18:39.779
[SCREAMING]

18:45.958 --> 18:48.791
When is the security guard
showing up?

18:50.195 --> 18:52.755
If I told you my kid has lice
and I might have it.

18:52.931 --> 18:55.456
I'm gonna rub my head
over every inch of this store...

18:55.634 --> 18:57.625
...is that gonna get him here
any faster?

18:57.803 --> 19:01.569
Hello? Hello?

19:01.740 --> 19:03.105
You can win this woman back.

19:03.275 --> 19:06.574
- You can go to her house right now.
- I don't know where she lives.

19:06.745 --> 19:09.111
I know it's somewhere in
New Mexico.

19:09.515 --> 19:12.848
I should have gotten her last name
back when we were in love.

19:13.018 --> 19:14.849
Wait. Is this just some
Internet woman?

19:15.020 --> 19:18.251
Just?
We danced for each other on iChat.

19:19.825 --> 19:21.759
She was the whole package.

19:21.927 --> 19:25.829
She had three kids. A little house.
A cat.

19:25.998 --> 19:28.967
I could have walked right in
and had a life.

19:30.435 --> 19:31.868
I could have been like you.

19:38.810 --> 19:42.769
So after the shift,
why don't you get some sleep...

19:42.948 --> 19:45.508
...then come by tomorrow night
for some dinner?

19:45.684 --> 19:48.983
- We'll put up some burgers.
- Really?

19:49.154 --> 19:50.815
Okay.

19:51.790 --> 19:54.759
I'd like that. Thanks, Mike.

19:57.329 --> 19:58.660
Can I tell you something...

19:58.830 --> 20:01.355
...I've never told anyone
in the whole world?

20:01.533 --> 20:03.125
No.

20:17.182 --> 20:18.581
There you are.

20:18.784 --> 20:22.220
<i>FRANKIE: Finally, Mike showed up
with the kids to make sure I got sprung.</i>

20:22.387 --> 20:25.379
<i>The Craigs had gotten their baby.
Brick got his lice medicine.</i>

20:25.557 --> 20:28.492
<i>Though she hadn't heard yet,
Sue was not feeling confident...</i>

20:28.660 --> 20:31.561
<i>...about her chances
of making majorettes.</i>

20:32.164 --> 20:36.260
Yeah, well,
I've had some time to think...

20:36.435 --> 20:38.869
...while I've been in here...

20:39.037 --> 20:41.665
...and I've figured out a few things...

20:41.840 --> 20:46.436
You know, I guess
there're some families somewhere...

20:46.612 --> 20:51.311
...where the moms don't have to yell,
but you know what?

20:51.750 --> 20:54.241
We're not one of them!

20:54.419 --> 20:57.946
Do you know why I pester and nag...

20:58.123 --> 21:02.059
...and get on your case,
and yell like a crazy person?

21:02.227 --> 21:04.354
Because nothing ever gets done
if I don't!

21:04.529 --> 21:06.724
So that's what we're going back to.

21:06.898 --> 21:09.230
I don't care
if it makes me look bad, I...

21:09.401 --> 21:12.199
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

21:13.972 --> 21:16.736
- What is she saying?
- I don't know.

21:16.908 --> 21:21.777
Just bow your heads.
Look ashamed.

21:23.982 --> 21:26.416
Now nod.
Nod like we know what she's saying.

21:35.093 --> 21:37.084
[ENGLISH - US - SDH]

